<HEADLINE> Belgium Names 22-man Squad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Belgian coach Georges Leekens
Saturday revealt his 22-man squad for the World Cup finals in
France.
</P>
<P>
Leekkens dropped three players from an initial squad of 25 he
named earlier. Defender Philippe Leonard of Monaco, midfielder
Gert Claessens of FC Brugge and striker Michael Goossens of
Schalke 04 missed out.
</P>
<P>
Belgium are in Group E with the Netherlands, South Korea and
Mexico in the finals.
</P>
<P>
The squad:
</P>
<P>
Goalkeepers: Filip De Wilde (Anderlecht), Philippe Vande Walle
(Aalst), Dany Verlinden (FC Brugge)
</P>
<P>
Defenders: Vital Borkelmans (FC Brugge), Philippe Clement
(Genk), Bertrand Crasson (Napoli), Glen De Boeck (Anderlecht),
Eric Deflandre (FC Brugge), Lorenzo Staelens (FC Brugge), Eric Van
Meir (Lierse), Mike Verstraeten (Germinal Ekeren), Gordan Vidovic
(Mouscron)
</P>
<P>
Midfielders: Danny Boffin (Metz), Enzo Scifo (Anderlecht),
Franky Van der Elst (FC Brugge), Nico Van Kerckhoven (Lierse),
Gert Verheyen (FC Brugge)
</P>
<P>
Forwards: Emile Mpenza (Standard Liege), Mbo Mpenza (Standard
Liege), Luc Nilis (PSV Eindhoven), Luis Oliveira (Fiorentina),
Marc Wilmots (Schalke 04). 
</P>
