<HEADLINE> Real Madrid Fine halved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Real Madrid have had their 200,000
U.S. dollars fine for crowd trouble at last month's European Cup
match with Borussia Dortmund halved, UEFA announced in Zurich on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
But a 1,000,000 Swiss francs (674,000 U.S. dollars) penalty for
apparently letting in too many fans stays.
</P>
<P>
A two-match ban on the home stadium has been cut to one. Real
must play their first home European game next season over 300
kilometers away from Madrid.
</P>
<P>
UEFA imposed the punishments following crowd problems at the
European Cup semi-final first leg against Borussia in Real's
Santaigo Bernabeu stadium on April 1.
</P>
<P>
Hooligans damaged one of the goals, causing a 75-minute delay.
</P>
</TEXT>
