<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria under Fire Back Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria, currently in Switzerland for
a World Cup training session, came under heavy fire back from home
after a series of disasterous performances in their preparations
for next month's event.
</P>
<P>
The "Super Eagles" chalked up an embarassing warming-up records
which have seen them tying Jamaica 2-2, losing to Germany 0-1,
humiliated 0-4 by the Swiss first division club Grasshoppers and
routed by Yugoslavia 0-3.
</P>
<P>
"Shame" and "Disaster" are the comments for the Olympic
champions from the already impatient Lagos media, who had
previously highly rated their World Cup-bound team.
</P>
<P>
The media also accused the national players of lacking
commitments, being loosely-minded and only seeking for personal
benefits.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria has now only one warm-up match before the World Cup,
taking them face the Netherlands on June 5. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
