<HEADLINE> U.S. Beats China 70-54 in Baskegball Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BREMEN, Germany, May 30 (Xinhua) -- WNBA star Lisa Leslie
scored a game-high 16 points and grabbed nine rebounds as the gold
medal favorite the United States nipped defending runner-up China
70-54 Saturday in group E of the Women's World Basketball
Championship second run.
</P>
<P>
The Americans, which topped group B at the preliminaries,
started a 16-5 led by Leslie's six points during the span of four
minutes into the game.
</P>
<P>
China, who was third in group matches with a win record, use a
8-0 spurt to cut the gap to 21-35 after Zheng Haixia, the MVP at
last championship and member of the WNBA, and guard Zheng Dongmei
entered the game off the bench.
</P>
<P>
Halftime ended 42-28 in favor of the Olympic gold medalists,
which composed of four WNBA players, seven members of American
Basketball Association and one from American college.
</P>
<P>
College star Chamique Holdsclaw added 13 points off the bench
for the United States. Center Ma Chengqing led China with 14
points and six rebounds while Haixia hit 9 points in her 21
minutes play.
</P>
<P>
The 12 teams from preliminay competition were divided into two
group for the second run matches. The United States, Russia,
Spain, Japan, China and Lithuania will play group E, while
Australia, Cuba, Gemany, Brazil, Slovakia, Hungary were in group
F. 
</P>
</TEXT>
