<HEADLINE> EU to Promote Cooperation with Iran: Former French </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Visiting former French President
Valery Giscard D'estaing said here on Sunday that the European
Union (EU) is to adopt a common policy on cooperation with Iran.
</P>
<P>
Addressing Tehran-based foreign diplomats and international
relations experts, D'estaing said that areas of cooperation
between the EU and Iran should be diversified.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that scientific and technical cooperation between
the two sides should continue through various means, saying that
the EU is considering a plan to determine new areas of
cooperation with Iran.
</P>
<P>
France and other European Union countries, Italy in particular,
are interested in improving relations with Iran, the former French
president said.
</P>
<P>
D'estaing, who arrived here on Friday for a three-day visit,
said the public opinion in Europe is positive toward the views and
statements of Iranian President Mohammad Khatami.
</P>
<P>
"We expect President Khatami to directly inform the European
people about his political and economic views," he said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed belief that Khatami's direct contacts with peoples
of different countries would help them know his views and bring
about mutual respect and better understanding between Iran and
other states. 
</P>
</TEXT>
