<HEADLINE> Wanda Draws Guo'an to Retain Lead in Chinese League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- League leader Dalian Wanda fought
Guo'an to a 1-1 away tie to keep its lead as Shanghai Shenhua also
tied 1-1 at home with unheralded Yanbian Aodong in the 12th round
of the Chinese soccer first division league.
</P>
<P>
Star striker Hao Haidong opened the scoring for Wanda in the
20th minute for the visitors to silence the sellout stadium before
Li Dongpo equalized with a surprise shot from outside the penalty
in the 39th minute.
</P>
<P>
Guo'an was outplayed by Wanda all the way through the
competition as Wanda controlled the midfield, forcing the host to
the defense. Guo'an only staged strong attacks during the opening
minutes in each half, highlighted by its speed advantage.
</P>
<P>
Shenhua remained three points adrift from Wanda in the
standings after it came a long way to overcome a 1-0 deficit with
a late goal in injury time, while Guangzhou Songri scored a
surprise 3-1 away win over star-studded Vanguard Huandao.
</P>
<P>
In the other games of the day, Shichuan Quanxing tied 1-1 with
Shenzhen Pingan. Zhuangyi scored his first goal in the league as
Qingdao Hainiu notched up a 1-0 win over the Chinese Army.
</P>
<P>
Shenyang Haishi held Shangdong Luneng to a 1-1 draw where the
imports came into the spotlight. Guangzhou Apollo was held
scoreless by Wuhan Hong Jinlong, facing the threat of being
demoted after it failed to exploit the host advantage. 
</P>
