<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian President Reiterates Call for Dialog </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad Khatami
Sunday reiterated his call for dialog among different
civilizations in the world, the Iranian official news agency IRNA
reported.
</P>
<P>
"We need to work to make the next century a time of dialog
among civilizations," Khatami said during a meeting with visiting
former French President Valery Giscard D'estaing.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the need to enter the 21st century with a new
outlook, saying that cultural and political personalities of the
world can be instrumental to help realize the dialog in the
world.
</P>
<P>
Khatami, a moderate advocate of reforms and social changes in
Iran, has repeated his call for dialog to promote understanding
among different cultures and civilizations on several occasions
since he took office last August.
</P>
<P>
D'estaing, who arrived here on Friday for a three-day visit,
said that France has viewed the election of Khatami among the
important events last year.
</P>
<P>
"We all want to see Iran find its rightful place in the world
community, and driven by this, we are keenly pursuing your
outlooks of world issues," he said.
</P>
<P>
Welcoming Khatami's initiative on dialog, the former French
president said that "one of the problems in this century is the
misconceptions existing among adherents of various schools of
thoughts with regard to each other."
</P>
<P>
"Nations and civilizations should respect each other, but
before that they should gain a thorough knowledge of each others'
cultures," he said, adding that the real face of Iran should be
introduced to the world and "I am delighted about being in Iran
and to be able to testify to the present realities in Iran."
</P>
</TEXT>
