quarter of this year compared with the 3.5 percent in the same
period last year due to lower consumption and stagnant investment,
the Arabic-language newspaper Al Hayat reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The paper did not give specific growth rate during the first
three months this year.
</P>
<P>
It said that the inflation rate during the period stood at 1.08
percent while public and private consumption dropped by 2 percent
compared with the same period in 1997.
</P>
<P>
DOHA -- A world investment company, the first of its kind in
Qatar, has been established, Egyptian daily Alam Al Yom reported
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Named "Salam," the company will undertake business in trade,
industry, education, tourism, real estate and finance. 
