<HEADLINE> Two Minor Quakes Hit Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Two minor earthquakes hit the
Chinese capital within five minutes this evening, according to the
State Seismological Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The quakes, both measuring 3.1 on the Ritcher Scale, occurred
at 7:37 and 7:42 this evening (local time), the bureau said.
</P>
<P>
It also said that the epicenter was located at around Fengtai
District, about 15 kilometers away from the center of Beijing, or
39.53 degrees north latitude and 116.18 degrees east longitude.
</P>
<P>
The quakes were felt in Fengtai, Shijingshan, Haidian and some
other areas of the Chinese capital.  
