<HEADLINE> Beijing Celebrates International Children's Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Three thousand pre-school children
from across the country gathered at the Tian'anmen Square in
central Beijing today to celebrate International Children's Day.
</P>
<P>
They performed exercises designed specially for pre-school
children to celebrate their own festival.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the performance, 4,000 pigeons which symbolize peace
and happiness were released to fly into the sky.
</P>
<P>
Among those present at the gathering were senior officials from
the Chinese National People's Congress (NPC), the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), the China Committee on Caring for the Younger
Generation and All-China Sports Federation, including Sun Fuling,
Wan Guoquan, Lei Jieqiong and Wu Shaozu.
</P>
<P>
An official from the China Committee for Caring for the Younger
Generation said that the committee has developed the setting-up
exercises, which were performed today at the Tian'anmen Square, to
help keep Chinese children fit and improve their overall quality.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that in Chinese cities, about 10 percent of
children under the age of six years are fatter than normal, and
that there are many children of the same age who are slimmer than
normal.
</P>
<P>
In 15 series, the exercises reportedly accord with the
psychological and physical characteristics of children aged
between three and six years, and are interesting and easy to
learn, the official said.
</P>
<P>
To date, hundreds of kindergartens in the country involving
more than 100,000 children have launched such exercises, according
to the official.
</P>
<P>
Today's gathering was sponsored by the China Committee for
Caring for the Younger Generation, the All-China Women's
Federation and All-China Sports Federation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
