<HEADLINE> Chinese Scientists Invited to Guide Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Twelve academicians of the Chinese
Academy of Sciences and the Chinese Academy of Engineering (CAE)
accepted invitations to be science and technology tutors for the
Chinese capital's one million primary and middle school students.
</P>
<P>
The name-list of the academicians, including Wang Daheng and
Zhu Guangya, president of CAE, was published today at a ceremony
to mark the founding of Beijing Jinpeng Science and Technology
Group.
</P>
<P>
Many Chinese scientists have noted that Chinese primary and
middle school students will find it hard to meet scientific and
technological competition of the next century as they are poor at
practical ability and lack knowledge of subjects other than
school-run courses.
</P>
<P>
The founding of the Beijing Jinpeng Science and Technology
Group, which includes ten sub-groups in astronomy, biological
engineering, electronics, aviation and space science, computer and
environmental protection and other areas, marks a major move of
the Chinese capital to raise the quality of students. 
</P>
</TEXT>
