<HEADLINE> 13,000 Beijing Residents Enter for Cross-Straits Abacus Contest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- More than 13,000 people in the
Chinese capital of Beijing today participated in a mail-based
cross-Straits abacus contest.
</P>
<P>
The number of participants is the largest since the annual
event was initiated in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Dexing, head of the Beijing Abacus Association, said that
this year's contest was restricted to workers and students and
Beijing and Taiwan used the same set of test paper and valuation
standards.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, a total of 33,000 people in Beijing
have taken part in the cross-Strait abacus contest, which is
jointly sponsored by the mainland-based China Abacus Association
and the Taiwan-based Chamber of Commerce. 
</P>
</TEXT>
