<HEADLINE> CAE Announces Criteria for Research Activities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Criteria for research activities
was announced today by the Chinese Academy of Engineering, with
academicians asked not to use their titles for the commercial
purpose.
</P>
<P>
The criteria require academicians not to become involved in any
kind of commercial advertisements by receiving free gifts, and
"when necessary, a state should be made."
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the criteria, all the academicians should
cherish the purity of their titles and set an example for others
to fellow through their good behaviors.
</P>
<P>
The criteria also stress that citations and sources must be
mentioned clearly in papers of academicians if their studies are
based on previous studies.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Academy of Sciences, another top science and
technology research institute in China, set up a moral committee
for scientific research in 1996, in an effort to check unhealthy
academic tendencies.
</P>
<P>
In June of 1997, when Chen Minheng, an academician of the
Chinese Academy of Sciences working for the East China Science and
Technology University, was found plagiarism, two investigations
were conducted soon.
</P>
<P>
As a result, Chen was asked to stop using his title as an
academy during the investigation.
</P>
<P>
Recently, Chen was asked to made a self-criticism to examine
his mistakes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
