<HEADLINE> 10 Rebels Killed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan Navy attacked four
boats of the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) at Chalai in
Northern province of the country Sunday, defense sources here
said.
</P>
<P>
The sources said at least 10 LTTE rebels were killed in the
attack while the four boats were badly damaged.
</P>
<P>
It was revealed that the boats were carrying injured LTTE
rebels, said the sources, adding that medicines and food items
were also found in these boats.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been fighting the government for a
separate state in the north and east of the country since 1983.
