<HEADLINE> Most-Advanced Hospital For Children Opens in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 31 (Xinhua) -- China's most modern hospital
for children opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Children's Medical Center, located in the city's
Pudong New Area, was built at a cost of 320 million yuan and
supplied by an American health fund with 20 million US dollars in
advanced medical equipment and five million US dollars for
personnel training.
</P>
<P>
The Hewlett-Packard Company of the United States also provided
for the center advanced medical instruments, such as systems for
monitoring patient and clinical data management.
</P>
<P>
The center, which is a subsidiary of the Shanghai No. 2 Medical
University, covers an area of 100 mu (about seven ha) and has 250
beds. It has more than 20 departments and can accommodate 250,000
child patients each year.
</P>
<P>
Many of the center's medical personnel have been trained in the
United States and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
At a special "Child Health Festival" launched today to mark the
opening of the medical center, more than 100 paediatricians from
China, the United States, Britain, Spain and Australia provided
consultance and gave lectures on child health care.  
</P>
</TEXT>
