<HEADLINE> One Third Of Urban Smokers Prefer Foreign Brands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- A latest survey shows that 30.8
percent of urban Chinese smokers prefer foreign-brand cigarettes
than local brands, and moreover, 21.1 percent of them smoke
foreign cigarettes only.
</P>
<P>
The survey was conducted by an information company under the
State Statistical Bureau among 1,000 local smokers in major
Chinese cities of Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou, Chengdu and Xi'an.
</P>
<P>
According to the investigation, 44.5 percent of smokers in
Beijing, the national capital, smoke more foreign cigarettes than
local brands, while only 19.5 percent of smokers in Xi'an,
capital of northwestern Shaanxi Province, prefer imported ones.
</P>
<P>
The survey also finds that most local smokers have little
knowledge of cigarette-smuggling. Only 48.7 percent of the urban
smokers surveyed said that they know the meaning of the label
"Monopoly by the China Cigarette Corp" on the packages of imported
cigarettes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
