<HEADLINE> African Kids Celebrate Children's Day in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Over 80 African children happily
attended a painting competition on the lawn at the Embassy of the
Republic of Congo in Beijing this afternoon to celebrate the
forthcoming International Children's Day and the African Day
which fell on May 25.
</P>
<P>
Many of the kids drew the paradises they have in mind with
unfettered imagination. Most of the paradises are characteristic
of the Africa-styled houses on the African continent. "I love
drawing houses because my home is a sweet home," said one kid from
Libya. " I hope all homes in Africa are peaceful," a girl from the
Republic of Congo said in answering why she painted so many
beautiful houses.
</P>
<P>
The competition, the first of its kind, was organized by the
African Association of Beijing, which "is aimed at promoting
exchanges and friendship within African community in Beijing and
with people of other countries," said M.Adil Embarch, chairman of
the African Association of Beijing.
</P>
<P>
"After experiences are gained from this competition, a second
one will be held next year in which children from outside Africa
will be invited," pledged Embarch, who is also first secretary of
the Moroccan embassy in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
