<HEADLINE> 6 Boys Killed by Grenade in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Six boys died after a hand
grenade they found exploded Saturday afternoon at a township near
Umtata, Eastern Cape province, South African Press Association
(SAPA) reported.
</P>
<P>
SAPA quoted an Eastern Cape police spokesman as saying Sunday
that eight boys were looking after livestock when they saw a boy
throw something into a field.
</P>
<P>
The boys went to investigate. One of them picked up the hand
grenade and passed it to his friends. While they were examining
the weapon, it exploded, killing six of the boys, aged between
nine and 16.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the hand grenade appeared to be an M26 of
South African origin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
