<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hingis Enters French Open Quarters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 31 (Xinhua) -- World top player Martina Hingis
became the first to reach the quarter-finals of the French Open on
Sunday when she beat Israel's Anna Smashnova 6-1, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
The 17-year-old Swiss sealed her fourth round match in one
hour, moving closer to claiming the grand slam title that she has
yet to win.
</P>
<P>
Despite being ranked 102th in the world, Smashnova, 21, had
some great marks under her credit by reaching the fourth round
here three years ago and winning claycourt tournaments in Athens
and Cardiff this year.
</P>
<P>
But Hingis, who lost last year's final to Croatian Iva Majoli,
posed as a too much obstacle for the Israeli with winners at will
from the baseline.
</P>
<P>
"She's playing unbelievable, I just couldn't keep up," said
Smashnova. "She doesn't give you anything, she's just on another
level."
</P>
<P>
For Hingis, she has breezed through her first four matches in
straight sets, surrendering only 14 games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
