<HEADLINE> Six Killed in Traffic Accident in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, May 31 (Xinhua) -- At least six people were killed
and 50 others seriously injured Sunday morning when a bus fell 400
feet (about 122 meters) down the road near Tansen, headquarters of
Palpa district in western Nepal, Radio Nepal said.
</P>
<P>
The injured are undergoing treatment at a local hospital, the
state-run radio said, adding that the police are investigating
into the accident.
</P>
<P>
In the past two weeks, more than one dozen people had died in
three separate accidents on the Palpa-Butwal route, which is no
more than 40 kilometres long. 
</P>
</TEXT>
