<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Grant Keeps IBC Heavyweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Unbeaten Michael Grant succeeded
in defending his IBC heavyweight title on Saturday night by
parlaying a late style adjustment into a ninth-round victory over
Obed Sullivan.
</P>
<P>
Grant floored Sullivan midway through the round with a
combination of punches highlighted by three jabs, a left hook and
a straight right, and finished the title defense with a series of
unanswered punches that prompted referee Tony Orlando to stop the
scheduled 12-round bout at 2:16 of the ninth.
</P>
<P>
Grant, 25, improved to 28-0 with 20 knockouts, and Sullivan,
30, fell to 29-3-1 with 20 knockouts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
