<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Wins Three Golds in World Cup Gymnastics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Liu Xuan, Zhang Jingjin and Li
Xiaopeng awarded three gold medals for China at the Gymnastics
World Cup finals in Sabae on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Liu Xuan, a 19-year-old from Hunan province, put on a near
perfect performance to score the best of 9.800 points in the beam
event to beat world champion Gina Gogean of Romania.
</P>
<P>
Her teammate Kui Yuanyuan helped China for a 1-2 finish in the
event in 9.762 points, while Gogean had to settle for a bronze
medal in 9.625 points.
</P>
<P>
World all-around champion Khorkina Svetlana of Russia was
fourth with 9.512 points.
</P>
<P>
"I was sure I had won it when I ended my performance," said
Liu, who had her best world silver medal in 1995 and the bronze
medal in 1996.
</P>
<P>
"I know I'm at the level that I can win the gold medal and I
gave 100 percent today. I didn't feel any pressure since our
athletes are at the top level in the world," Liu said.
</P>
<P>
The other gold medals for China were through Zhang Jingjin and
Li Xiaopeng in the men's parallel bars.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese duo shared the top honour with Alexei Dimitrienko
of Kazakhstan with an identical 9.575 points.
</P>
<P>
In women's floor exercise, Romania Simona Amanar defeated her
compatriot world champion Gina Gogean for her second victory here
following her vault gold medal Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Alena Polozkova of Belarus took the bronze while world silver
medallist Khorkina ended fourth.
</P>
<P>
Olympic vault champion Alexei Nemov collected 9.581 points to
beat fellow Russian Alexei Bondarenko and win the vault gold,
while the horizontal bar title went to world all-around champion
Ivan Ivankov of Belarus.
</P>
<P>
After 10-event competition, China took six gold medals, Romania
three, Russia, France, Belarus, Kazakhstan and Hungary one
each. 
</P>
</TEXT>
