<HEADLINE> Minor Quake Hits Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- A minor earthquake, less than 3 on
the Ritcher scale, hit the Chinese capital city of Beijing at
around 7:40 this evening (local time).
</P>
<P>
The epicenter was said to be at Babaoshan area, about 15
kilometers away from the center of Beijing, according to the State
Seismological Bureau.
</P>
<P>
No other details are available so far. 
</P>
