<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Becker To Skip Wimbeldon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Boris Becker, a three-time Wimbledon
champion, said on Saturday that he definitely would not plan to
play at the grand slam event this year.
</P>
<P>
Becker said during an interview on German television late
Saturday that "people should get used to the idea that the tennis
player Boris Becker belongs to the past."
</P>
<P>
Becker, now in semi-retirement, had announced after losing to
Pete Sampras in the quarter-finals at Wimbledon last year that he
would not play the tournament again to be started on June 22.
</P>
<P>
However, in recent months he had hinted that he might return
this year after all.
</P>
<P>
Becker, now Germany's Davis Cup team manager, won the Wimbeldon
singles in 1985, 1986 and 1989. 
</P>
</TEXT>
