<HEADLINE> Peruzzi to Miss World Cup Finals for Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Italy's first-choice goalkeeper Angelo
Peruzzi will miss the upcoming World Cup finals after he injured
his left calf muscle in Sunday's training.
</P>
<P>
"I'm very upset. Now I'll have to sweat another four years to
go to the next World Cup," Peruzzi said after he sustained the
injury at the training camp in Coverciano near Florence.
</P>
<P>
The Juventus goalkeeper fell to the ground in obvious pain
after jumping for a ball in a morning practice session. Team
doctors and reserve goalkeeper Gianluca Pagliuca immediately
rushed to his aid.
</P>
<P>
Valentini said that Fiorentina's goalkeeper Francesco Toldo
will replace Peruzzi and Pagliuca will become Italy's first choice
goalkeeper.
</P>
<P>
Peruzzi did not compete in the 1994 World Cup finals but has
played for his club over the past three sessions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
