<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Industry Grows in First Five Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's industrial production grew
by 12.7 percent to about 4.58 billion U.S. dollars in the first
five months of this year from that of the same period last year,
official statistics showed.
</P>
<P>
But in Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam's industrial hub, industrial
production grew by just 5.9 percent, about half that for the first
five months of last year.
</P>
<P>
The figures showed that it will be very difficult to meet this
year's industrial growth target of 13.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
"The Vietnam Economic Times" said inefficiency, outdated
equipment and a chronic lack of capital to upgrade technology are
the major reasons for the slowdown.
</P>
<P>
Ninety percent of the industrial sector's capital comes from
loans and this is aggravating the difficulties, especially as the
prices for industrial goods was lower than anticipated, according
to the weekly magazine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
