<HEADLINE> Thousands Feared Dead in Strong Quake in Afghanistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Thousands of people were feared
dead Sunday after a strong earthquake measuring 6.9 on the Richter
scale jolted northeastern Afghanistan on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here Sunday from the Afghan capital of Kabul
said that about 50 villages were destroyed in the earthquake which
centered around Rostaq and Faizabad in the mountainous region.
</P>
<P>
However, the reports said the casualties were expected to be
lower than those in February's quake in the same region because
Saturday's took place in the morning when many people were out of
their homes.
</P>
<P>
The February earthquake measuring 6.4 on the Ritcher scale
occurred in the night. It destroyed 14 villages and killed about
3,500 people.
</P>
<P>
According to the reports, international aid workers were trying
to reach Badakhshan in northern Afghanistan to try to assess the
extent of the damage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
