<HEADLINE> Shanghai Industrial Climate Improves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 31 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey shows that the
industrial climate in east China's Shanghai municipality, a
leading manufacturing base in the country, improved significantly
in the second quarter of this year.
</P>
<P>
More than half of the industrial firms said that the
macro-economic environment and their operation conditions are
good, according to the survey conducted by the Shanghai
Information Center, said.
</P>
<P>
The survey attributed the improvement to more orders, larger
output and abundant supply of energy and raw materials.
</P>
<P>
The survey also noted that sectors such as tobacco, textile and
garment enjoyed improvement in the operational climate, while the
food processing and printing businesses are still in a cloudy
climate.
</P>
<P>
This also indicated that the municipal industrial firms are
confident with the set economic growth target, said the survey.
</P>
<P>
The survey admitted that many manufacturing firms still face
serious fund shortage problems.  
</P>
