<HEADLINE> Vicious Flu Virus Hits S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, May 31 (Xinhua) -- An extremely vicious
influenza virus is sweeping through South Africa, increasing
intakes at hospitals and clinics, forcing some schools to close
and hitting industry with high percentage of absenteeism.
</P>
<P>
While it has been difficult to get figures of the affected,
experts confirm that large numbers are in sick beds.
</P>
<P>
The outbreak of flu has led to a sharp drop in blood supplies
at the South African Blood Transfusion Service (SABTS) because
many donors have fallen ill, according to the City Press weekly
newspaper.
</P>
<P>
In the past two weeks, SABTS received only 6,000 units, only
half of the 12,000 units it would normally have received.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted SABTS spokesman Diane de Coning as saying
that flu has disabled many regular donors and the agency is
appealing to healthy people to donate blood.
</P>
<P>
Medical experts have warned that the flu, although not
dangerous in itself, could lead to life-threatening complications
such as pneumonia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
