<HEADLINE> Shanghai Private Firms Improve Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 31 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shanghai municipality
now has some 240 private firms which were funded by foreign
investors and another 2,500 such firms which are engaged in
export-oriented processing operations or foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
This indicated that the private firms in the municipality have
upgraded their operation by joining in international competition,
noted local government officials.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the local government also show that in 1997
only, more than 1,500 private firm owners went abroad for further
expansion, generating more than one billion yuan in foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
Operational improvement of these firms was also shown in the
respect of the general quality of the owners and the emerging of
firms engaged in high-tech industries.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai now has 74,000 private firms, of which, five percent
are engaged in technological undertakings. The rate doubled the
country's average. Meanwhile, 18 percent of the owners of the
private firms in the municipality have a college education
background, statistics show.  
</P>
