<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The recent formation of a
Sino-Swiss joint venture has initiated foreign capital
participation in China's overseas tourism services.
</P>
<P>
The Yunnan Diethem Tourism Co. Ltd was established by China
International Travel Service (CITS), Yunnan Tourism Co. Ltd and
Diethem Company of Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
"We will attract tourists from the United States, Japan and
European countries to Yunnan Province, taking advantage of our
tourism networks in Southeast Asia," said Luzi Matzig, deputy
chairman of the Yunnan Diethem Tourism Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss company, which covers such business as trade,
manufacturing, pharmaceuticals, and cosmetics, serves as the
general agent in Southeast Asia for more than 30 European tourism
companies.
</P>
<P>
CITS is the country's biggest tourism agency, reporting 1.5
billion yuan in business volume and receiving 400,000 tourists
annually, while the Yunnan company is the leading tourism service
in the province.
</P>
<P>
Tourism in the province has maintained an average annual
increase of 10 percent in recent years. Last year, it received
800,000 overseas tourists, earning 260 million US dollars, and 24
million domestic tourists also visited Yunnan. 
</P>
