<HEADLINE> East China City Reports Rising Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Jinan, capital of Shandong Province
of east China, signed contracts with overseas investors involving
44 million U.S. dollars of overseas investment in the first four
months this year, 4.5 times the figure for the same period last
year.
</P>
<P>
Local sources said that the actual paid-in sum of overseas
investment during the period stood at 108 million U.S. dollars, a
rise of 45.7 percent over last year's comparable figure.
</P>
<P>
Meng Jianxin, director of the Jinan Commission of Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation, attributed the boom in overseas
investment despite the East Asian financial crisis to the fact
that the city has changed the past practice of focusing efforts
only in attracting overseas investment to industrial processing
projects for broadening investment scope, and a list containing
municipal infrastructure, comprehensive agricultural development
and high- and new-technological projects for overseas investors
has been prepared.
</P>
<P>
Upgrading, building and transfer of operation rights of
municipal infrastructure have become popular destination of
overseas investment, the director continued to explain.
</P>
<P>
For instance, to improve water shortage in Jinan, the city will
expand three existing water plants, construct one new water plant,
replenish shortage of underground water resources by diverting the
flow of the Yellow River this year in cooperation with investors
from Britain and the United States.
</P>
<P>
The projects require a total investment of 118 million
U.S. dollars. So far, 40 million U.S. dollars of overseas
investment have been paid in for first-phase construction.
</P>
<P>
Shandong Province had altogether approved establishment of
20,000 overseas-financed projects with contracts involving an
agreed use of 36.5 billion U.S. dollars of overseas investment by
1997. And the actual paid-in sum of overseas investment was at
20.2 billion U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
