<HEADLINE> Poor Farmers Move out of Mountains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, May 31 (Xinhua) -- More than 61,000 poor farmers living
in mountains in east China's Fujian province have moved out to
settle in plain areas to enjoy better living conditions, thanks to
the local government's efforts.
</P>
<P>
These poor farmers, living in the eastern part of the province,
suffered from a hostile natural environment and backward transport
facilities.
</P>
<P>
The local government began to allocate funds to move them out
of the mountains in 1994. In 1997 only, the local government
invested 100 million yuan for this purpose.
</P>
<P>
Four years passed and 61,800 people in more than 10,000
households bade farewell to their old residences as well as
poverty.
</P>
<P>
The per capita income for those farmers also increased to more
than 1,000 yuan in 1997 from the former 200 yuan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
