<HEADLINE> Dhaka, New Delhi Sign Accord on Border Demarcation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh and India have agreed to
expedite the process of border demarcation, the independent United
News of Bangladesh (UNB) reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached on Saturday at the end of a border
conference between the two neighboring South Asian countries,
which was convened from May 26 to 30 in the Indian capital, New
Delhi, UNB quoted an official press release as saying.
</P>
<P>
During the conference, the two sides discussed the issues of
firing and killing by the Border Security Forces of India in the
border areas and trans-border crimes, the release said.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed the issues of exchanging enclaves and
adversely-held lands.
</P>
<P>
Regarding insurgency, both sides have decided to take necessary
steps to implement the stands of the two governments not to allow
the use of their territories by the insurgents against each other,
the release added. 
</P>
