<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Forsaken Snow Leopards Fed By Dog </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Three newly-born snow leopards,
Forsaken by their mother leopard more than a week ago, are now in
good health conditions as they are properly fed by a dog,
according to sources from Beijing Zoo.
</P>
<P>
Their weight has grown to 855, 890 and 670 grams respectively
from former 575, 515 and 450 grams when they were born on May 17.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the zoo said that the mother leopard had showed no
interest to feed its babies eight hours after little snow leopards
were born.
</P>
<P>
Sources from Beijing Zoo said that the reason that the mother
leopard did not want to feed its babies was possiblly because of
the noisy environment.
</P>
<P>
Animal keepers at Beijing Zoo found a dog mother for the three
snow leopards in the dog-raising center in suburban Beijing's
Changping county on May 19. The dog just gave births to tree
puppies on May 15.
</P>
<P>
The dog is expected to feed the snow leopards in the zoo for at
least one month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
