<HEADLINE> Private Firms Growing Fast in Liaoning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The number of newly-registered
private firms in northeast China's Liaoning province grew by 50
percent in the first two months of this year compared with the
same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
So far, more than 50,000 private firms are operating in this
heavy industrial center which used to be dominated by the
state-owned sector.
</P>
<P>
It was a result of flexible measures for smaller state-owned
firms worked out by the central government.
</P>
<P>
Many small state-owned enterprises have been auctioned at fairs
held in Xiamen, Shenzhen and Beijing cities.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning Provincial Governor Zhang Guoguang said anyone who can
invigorate an enterprise will be allowed to buy it.  
