<HEADLINE> Hunting Ethnic Group Changes to Businesses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- People of the Jingpo ethnic group,
traditional hunters mainly residing in southwest China's Yunnan
pProvince, now pay more attention to business operations.
</P>
<P>
This ethnic group, with a population of 200,000, lives in the
Dehong Autonomous Prefecture of Dai and Jingpo Nationalities.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the prefecture now has 370 individual
businesses, with a combined annual business volume of nearly 40
million yuan (4.8 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Dong Lecheng is one of the most successful businessmen of the
Jingpos.
</P>
<P>
At present, his company, which is engaged in commerce and
services, boasts a capital of close to 100 million yuan (some 12
million US dollars), the tenth biggest among Yunnan's private
businesses.
</P>
<P>
He is called by local people as the "naoshuang", which means
the "leader", because he is first among Jingpos to engage in
business.
</P>
<P>
Li Zhiming, deputy director of the Dehong Autonomous Prefecture
of Dai and Jingpo Nationalities, said that before 1985 there was
no Jingpo business, because they thought doing business was a
disgraced thing.
</P>
<P>
Li Zhiming said that it is the opening environment that leads
Jingpo people to do business.
</P>
<P>
At present, one-third of Jingpo families have moved from
mountainous areas to places where they enjoy convenience in doing
businesses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
