<HEADLINE> China to Step up Chemical Industrial Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 31 (Xinhua) -- An official in charge of China's
petroleum and chemical industry says that 29 large and
medium-sized chemical industrial projects will start operation
within the year.
</P>
<P>
Li Yongwu, director of the State Bureau of Petroleum and
Chemical Industry, said economic returns of these projects is very
important to the planned 8 percent growth of the industry.
</P>
<P>
Of the 29 projects, 11 are infrastructure facilities, and the
other 18 are designed to upgrade the technology of existing
operations.
</P>
<P>
The new projects are expected to add a production capacity of
1.2 million tons of chemical ores, 1.55 million tons of
fertilizers, 220,000 tons of synthetic materials, 40,000 tons of
organic materials, and 200,000 tires.
</P>
<P>
In veiw of fixed assets investment expansion in the national
economy as a whole, Li said, "the chemical industry will increase
investment as well, and work to step up the construction of
infrastructures and technology upgrading."
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Government plans to invest 3.08 trillion yuan in
fixed assets this year.
</P>
<P>
Of the investment in chemical industrial fixed assets, 6.5
billion yuan will be used in 11 projects that will be completed
this year, and five projects whose construction will continue next
year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 1.7 billion yuan will be put in 67 large and
medium-sized projects that will break ground this year, including
20 infrastructure facilities and 47 technology upgrading items.
</P>
<P>
A nylon project in Pingdingshan of central China's Henan
Province involving 2.93 billion yuan will become operational in
1998, and is set to be able to produce 65,000 tons of nylon and 10
million tons of color concentrates for plastics a year.
</P>
<P>
A triple superphosphate project in southwest China's Guizhou
province will start operation. It is expected to have an annual
production capacity of 800,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Experts say the impact of investment increase on economic
activities will be evident after a period of time. They predict
the national economy will show a strong growth momentum in the
second and third quarters this year.
</P>
<P>
The total output of the chemical industry will have a 5 percent
growth to reach 145.5 billion yuan. The growth in the second half
of the year will be faster, and the yearly 8 percent growth target
will be achieved.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, 29 infrastructure and technology upgrading projects
started operation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
