<HEADLINE> Central Chinese Province to Use More Foreign Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Henan Province
will absorb large amounts of investment from abroad this year to
accelerate its economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Overseas companies are welcome to invest in such traditional
pillar industries as electronics, machine-building,
pharmaceuticals, textiles and chemicals in Henan, said Zhang
Yixiang, vice-governor of Henan, at a provincial conference.
</P>
<P>
They may also develop high-efficient agricultural and forest
projects, build communications and power supply projects, urban
engineering facilities and sewage disposal projects.
</P>
<P>
Other sectors open to overseas investors include new and
high-tech development, export-oriented industries, construction of
industrial parks and renovation of old urban residential areas.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, more than 5,790 foreign-funded firms
had been built in Henan, involving a total contractual value of 7
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Previously, over 80 percent of overseas investment came from
the Republic of Korea, the Association of Southeast Asian Nations,
Hong Kong and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
As from this year, Zhang said, the provincial government is to
adopt a multi-outlet policy and enhance contacts with north
America, West European countries and Japan. 
</P>
