<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ecuador Ready to Keep Order in Presidential Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Fourteen thousand policemen have been
ready to keep order in the Ecuadoran presidential elections to be
held Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Interior Minister Edgar Rivadeneira said Saturday that there will
be full coordination among the armed forces, police and the
Supreme Electoral Court to keep watch outside the voting boots.
</P>
<P>
They will also detour vehicles and enforce the compliance with
the law that prohibits sales of alcoholic beverages.
</P>
<P>
In an open letter, Catholic Church Cardinal Bernardino
Echeverria called on citizens to take part in Sunday's voting.
</P>
<P>
"We cannot play with the future. We must choose a man with
experience who can unite Ecuadorans as the Church demands it, some
one who can stop the violence, the lies and the demagogy," added
the clergyman. 
</P>
