<HEADLINE> 224 Die of Diseases in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, May 31 (Xinhua) -- An outbreak of pneumonia,
gastroenteritis and fever during the summer season have claimed
224 lives in 45 villages of 15 districts in Nepal, the Health
Ministry said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
And 6,646 others are said to be affected by the seasonal
diseases in the underdeveloped parts of the country, which include
the western part and the Terai region bordering India.
</P>
<P>
Unhygienic living conditions, contaminated drinking water and
lack of medicine and awareness are blamed for the outbreak of
diseases, the ministry said.
</P>
<P>
Compared with previous years, the death toll has gone up this
year, especially in the remote hilly districts in the western part
of the country.
</P>
<P>
Medical teams have been dispatched to the affected areas, the
ministry said.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that there is a food shortage in some affected
districts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
