<HEADLINE> Uruguayan Beef Exports Up in First Four Months and Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Uruguayan meat export earned 195
million U.S. dollars in the first four months, the National Meat
Institute data said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Beef export increased 6 percent to 104,500 tons over the same
period of last year, but mutton export dropped by 38 percent to 4,578
tons.
</P>
<P>
About 738,000 heads of cattle and 65,800 sheep were slaughtered
this year.
</P>
<P>
Meat is an important export item for Uruguay. The country sold
270,000 tons of beef to foreign nations in 1997, with an income of
385 million dollars. 
