<HEADLINE> United States Ties Scotland in World Cup Tune-up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Scotland and the United States
played to a 0-0 draw here Saturday in their last tune-up before
the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Scotland will play in the World Cup curtain-raiser on June 10
against title-favorite Brazil and also face Norway and Morocco in
the first round.
</P>
<P>
The draw was Scotland's third in as many matches, following a
2-2 tie with Colombia one week ago and a 1-1 finish with Finland
in April.
</P>
<P>
The United Staets will meet Germany in Paris on June 15 and
take on Iran and Yugoslavia in the first round. 
</P>
