<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Czech Catches 82 Kilos of Heroin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, May 30 (Xinhua) -- The Czech customs seized 82
kilograms of high-purity heroin at the border post of Lanzhor
leading to Slovakia on Saturday and arrested three suspects.
</P>
<P>
The drug seized amounts to three million koruny (about 2.28
million U.S. dollars), the second largest after an April
crackdown in which the Czech police captured 120 kilograms of
heroin.
</P>
<P>
Hidden in containers holding textiles, the heroin was being
transported from Turkey, a spokesperson of the Czech customs said.
</P>
<P>
Located at the heart of Europe, the Czech Republic has been
used recently by smugglers as a distribution center of heroin and
cocaine.
</P>
<P>
The Czech police has enhanced its forces in a bid to fight the
rising wave of narcotic smuggling. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
