<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Africa, Stuttgard Kickers Play to 1-1 Draw </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 30 (Xinhua) -- World Cup qualifier South Africa was
held to a 1-1 draw by lowly second division German side Stuttgart
Kickers on Saturday in Oberthal, southern Germany.
</P>
<P>
South African team captain midfielder Lucas Radebe scored the
27th minute when the team was awarded a freekick. But the lead
was cancelled when Tomislav Maric scored for Kickers in the 69th
minute.
</P>
<P>
The match was a disappointing performance by the South Africans
who were to compete in the World Cup finals for the first time
next month. They seemed to resort to playing a close-knit passing
game when it would have been more effective to go for goal.
</P>
<P>
Two players are to be chopped from the South African team on
Sunday before coach Philippe Troussier form his 22-man final World
Cup squad.
</P>
<P>
The team is scheduled to play the Iceland national team on June
6 in its last warm-up match before the World Cup finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
