<HEADLINE> Italy Concerned About Nuclear Tests in South Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi
said in a meeting in Milan Saturday that his government was deeply
concerned about the continuous nuclear tests in South Asia,
reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Also at the meeting, Deputy Prime Minister Walter Veltroni
expressed his worriness over the matter, saying they have posed
threats to world peace.
</P>
<P>
The Italian news agency ANSA reported Saturday that Italian
foreign ministry officials said new actions should be taken to end
the nuclear arms race in the region.
</P>
<P>
Italy supports Britain's proposal to hold a foreign ministers
meeting of the Group of Eight on the issue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
