<HEADLINE> Ujpest Takes Hungarian Soccer Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Ujpest won the Hungarian soccer
league for the first time in eight years as they drew Videoton 1-1
on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
An 85th-minute goal from Goran Kopunovic earned Ujpest a point
but the celebrations began when news came through from Budapest of
Ferencvaros' surprise 4-1 defeat by MTK Budapest.
</P>
<P>
