<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spain Down Japan at Women's Basketball Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BREMEN, Germany, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Spain pulled away from
midway of the game to beat Japan 97-58 in their opening match of
the second run competition at the Women's World Basketball
Championship here Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
Japan, which had upset Lithuania and placed second in
preliminary group, kept their pace in the opening minutes and
never trailed by more than five points until Spaniards made a 8-0
run for a 36-27 lead with 6:11 left in the first half.
</P>
<P>
Returning from locker room at 50-36, the Spanish team, second
placers in group A, extended the advantage while Japan fielded
their benchers with 12 minutes remaining.
</P>
<P>
Guard Anula Nieves led Spain in scoring board with 23 points,
followed by center Elisabeth Cebrian's 11.
</P>
<P>
Center Takako Kato scored 16 points and Mutsuko Nagata added 12
for Japan.
</P>
<P>
The 12 teams from preliminary competition were split into two
groups for the second run matches.
</P>
<P>
The United States, Russia, Spain, Japan, China and Lithuania
play in group E. Australia, Cuba, Germany, Brazil, Slovakia,
Hungary are bundled in group F. The top four sides from each group
enter the quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
Japan meet Russia and Spain take on the United States on
Sunday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
