<HEADLINE> Russia Rallies to Edge Lithuania, 61-52 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BREMEN, Germany, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Russia edged European
champions Lithuania 61-52 Saturday in a sea-saw game at the
opening day of the women's world baksektball championship second
run competition.
</P>
<P>
Eleva Baranova contributed 15 points and nine rebounds and
teammate Nata Zassoulskaya added 13 points and seven rebounds for
the Russians, who entered the second run with a 3-0 record in
group A,
</P>
<P>
Russia had tied Lithuania seven times before their rivals built
a 32-29 lead.
</P>
<P>
The second half also witnessed a see-saw game. Russia took
over 34-32 on Svetlana Antipova's fast break basket less than two
minutes after the interval and they never trailed.
</P>
<P>
But the victory did come easily as the score was equalized five
times before Russia, sixth-place finishers at the European
championship, surged ahead 54-50.
</P>
<P>
Jurgi Streimikyte and Jolanta Vilutyte were the leading scorers
for Lithuania with 12 points apeice. Streimikyte also grabbed
seven rebounds.  
</P>
</TEXT>
