<HEADLINE> Central Chinese Province Finds New Way To Help The Disabled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hunan Province is
beginning to help people with disabilities by requiring all
government departments, social bodies, institutions, and companies
to set aside 1.5 percent of their job opportunites for them.
</P>
<P>
Those who fail to give employment to the disabled people will
have to pay into a special foundation for the disabled, according
to the province's federation of the disabled.
</P>
<P>
The province has one million disabled people living below the
poverty line, and 881,500 of whom could make a living if they had
some help.
</P>
<P>
The federation says that banks will also be encouraged to
provide loans for disabled people to start profit-making projects.
</P>
<P>
China allocated 1.5 billion yuan for poverty relief this year,
a third of that going to disabled people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
