<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 30 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake measuring 6.9
on the Richter scale jolted northeastern Afghanistan Saturday,
according to a report by the Associated Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted the U.S. Geological Survey in Folden,
Colorado, as saying the location of the quake was in an area about
70 kilometers west of Faizabad, northeastern Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
