<BODY>
<HEADLINE> British Companies Doing Well In Coastal Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Britain is the biggest west European
investor in China's coastal Fujian province, with 944 million US
dollars worth of funds putting in 67 companies, according to a
provincial official.
</P>
<P>
He says that their average investment is above 16 million US
dollars, 5 times the average of any foreign-funded companies, and
that 21 of them have 10 million US dollars worth of investment
each.
</P>
<P>
These companies are involved in a wide range of areas like
electronics, machinery, petrochemicals, building materials,
construction, transportation, and trade.
</P>
<P>
They are also doing well generally, and 5 are among the 50 most
profitable foreign-funded companies in the province, the official
says. 
</P>
