<HEADLINE> Tunis Stock Index Gains Minor Rise in Last Trading </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, May 30 (Xinhua) -- The index of the Tunis Stock Exchange
rose slightly in the last trading week from May 25 to 29,
according to figures released by the stock exchange on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The index closed at 462.32 points on Friday, gaining a minor
0.02 points, the figures showed.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover in the week stood at 266,270 shares, whose
value amounted to 7.26 million Tunis dinars (roughly valued the
same as in U.S. dollar), 850,000 dinars more than that in the
previous trading week.
</P>
<P>
The shares that achieved moderate gains are those of Sofi Sikaf
Company, the Company for Land and Contributions, Tunisia Airlines,
the Tunisian Company for Employment, the Tunisian Company for
Investment and the Mechanized Laboratories by the Seashore.
</P>
<P>
The shares that declined are mainly those of financial sectors,
including the Security Bank, the Tunisian Bank, Tunisia
International Bank, the Tunisian Bank Firm and the Insurance
Company. 
</P>
</TEXT>
