<HEADLINE> Iranian Leader Calls for Unity of Political </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Supreme Leader Ayatollah Ali
Khamenei Saturday called for unity among political factions, the
Iranian official news agency IRNA reported.
</P>
<P>
Such a unity is needed to preserve the Islamic principles and
values, Khamenei told the members of Majlis (Parliament) on the
eve of its annual internal elections to decide the presiding board.
</P>
<P>
Reports have said that different political factions have been
busy with preparing for the elections due on Sunday, but none of
them has announced candidate.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that the conservative Majlis Speaker Ali Akbar
Nateq-Nouri would be re-elected for another one-year term since
the Majlis is controlled by the conservatives.
</P>
<P>
The pro-moderate daily Iran News said on Saturday that the
moderates have not reached a consensus over the elections due to
"the lack of harmony within the faction."
</P>
<P>
Moderate factions joined efforts to help Mohammad Khatami, an
advocate of social reforms and freedom, win the presidential
election in May last year. Ever since then, Iran sees frequent
factional struggles.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei said the realization of Islamic principles would help
strengthen the bond between the people and the government, which
would also help the country overcome problems. 
</P>
