<HEADLINE> Greece Launches New Consumer Hot Line for Complaints </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Greece has launched a new nationwide
consumer hot line for complaints and for product information.
</P>
<P>
The telephone number is part of a new system for codifying and
dealing with complaints as soon as possible, and the system will
relay consumers' complaints directly back to the traders or
manufacturers to achieve a speedy and out-of-court settlement of
differences, the Greek daily newspaper Kathimerini reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In Greece, 1998 has been declared Year of Quality, but public
and private sectors continue to pay more attention to prices
rather than to quality, variety, cleanliness or service.
</P>
<P>
According to a survey conducted recently by the Greek
Consumers' Federation (GOKE), a total of 30,155 complaints were
reported in the first five months of this year, mainly related to
the retail trade.
</P>
<P>
There were also complaints about banking services and credit
cards, public transport, water and electricity supply and car
repairs. 
</P>
