<DATE_TIME> 1998-05-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada Condemns Pakistan Nuclear Tests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, May 30 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Foreign Affairs Minister
Lloyd Axworthy condemned the latest series of nuclear tests
announced Saturday by Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistan government's decision to carry out another series
of nuclear tests "is a highly irresponsible act," Axworthy said in
a news release.
</P>
<P>
"It further increases tension in the region, and threatens
international security and the nuclear non-proliferation regime,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan carried out its first round of tests on May 28,
following the earlier tests by India.
</P>
<P>
Axworthy appealed to Pakistan and India to sign the Nuclear
Non-proliferation Treaty and the Comprehensive Nuclear Test Ban
Treaty.
</P>
<P>
The minister urged both countries to renew regional dialogue
and work toward a peaceful resolution of differences.
</P>
<P>
He also welcomed Britain's proposal to convene a meeting of G-8
foreign ministers on June 12 in London to discuss the issue, and
indicated that he plans to attend. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
