<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria Donates $100m to African Development Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, May 30 (Xinhua) -- The Nigerian government has donated
100 million U.S. Dollars to the Nigeria Trust Fund administered
by the African Development Bank (ADB) for the provision of soft
loans to poor African countries.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Omar Kabbaji, President of the ADB at a
news conference Friday in Abidjan, Cote d'Ivoire, according to
Saturday's Daily Times newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The Nigeria Trust Fund was set up by the Nigerian government
in 1976 with an initial capital base of 71 million Dollars to
provide credit facility to needy African countries.
</P>
<P>
The fund has allocated over 400 million Dollars in resources.
However, it has remained dormant in recent times, only one loan
was granted in 1996 and none last year, according to the ADB.
</P>
</TEXT>
